<subSubSection id="3C193FDB2A54B43567F3022FDEB8622D" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="A2E2A78ECB7F2BDD84FEB4A8CDBC32FA" pageId="21" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0CECE7D7AD6F2E65B9A9F71FAA276F68" pageId="21" pageNumber="36">
Although 
<bibRefCitation id="D88FBAF16173600A6463B26718434052" author="Lourenco, WR" journalOrPublisher="Revista Iberica de Aracnologia" pageId="31" pageNumber="46" pagination="9 - 14" title="Confirmation of a new species of Buthus Leach, 1815 from Sicily (Scorpiones, Buthidae). Biogeographical implications." volume="22" year="2013">
<normalizedToken id="9A3143A67991BE676FE84DA5BB4E0371" originalValue="Lourenço">Lourenco</normalizedToken>
and Rossi (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
report that the collector is not mentioned in Simon's notes, 
<bibRefCitation id="CCABF1EDCE5D107DFE8AF980697B868C" author="Kraepelin, K" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris" pageId="30" pageNumber="45" pagination="265 - 274" title="Catalogue des Scorpions des collections du Museum d'histoire naturelle de Paris." volume="7" year="1901">Kraepelin (1901)</bibRefCitation>
, in his list of all the scorpion material present in the MNHN Paris, writes that Letourneur collected the 
<taxonomicName id="12ECA402B3CAA5A217BD5D49DFD20E22" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
material from Sicily and Corfu (Greece), which causes doubts regarding the correct collection locality of the specimens used to describe this species. 
<bibRefCitation id="A9C4FF0DB793F8ABF631FF8A4090F05B" pageId="21" pageNumber="36">Simon (1879)</bibRefCitation>
had doubts about the actual existence of 
<taxonomicName id="0F679F31355C3D7D9E545591AEFB92EB" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
in Sicily (when examining the specimens that would eventually be designated as type material for 
<taxonomicName id="72444A4178D9999A79A39BBECEA50476" genus="B." lsidName="B. trinacrius" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" rank="species" species="trinacrius">B. trinacrius</taxonomicName>
): &quot;il habite probablement aussi le midi de 
<normalizedToken id="2CF6C5621DE0DC8F24DFC917B2F363E6" originalValue="l’Italie">l'Italie</normalizedToken>
et la Sicile&quot;, and 
<taxonomicName id="27443BE7B904E7417DB930CAB71EE40B" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
has never been found in mainland Italy. Furthermore, the authors also claimed that 
<bibRefCitation id="136406F1685E2A219FCE7069BE3AB906" author="Simon, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de d'Egypte" pageId="34" pageNumber="49" pagination="57 - 87" title="Revision des Scorpions d'Egypte." volume="2" year="1910">Simon (1910)</bibRefCitation>
&quot;referred to the almost impossibility to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="2E2BC0B4EBC234D1E6CAE05C4554D244" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
populations from North of Africa with those from Spain and Sicily&quot;, which is only partially correct. 
<bibRefCitation id="C757BED4462C8E444741748FE815B705" author="Simon, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de d'Egypte" pageId="34" pageNumber="49" pagination="57 - 87" title="Revision des Scorpions d'Egypte." volume="2" year="1910">Simon (1910)</bibRefCitation>
solely refered to the distinction of 
<taxonomicName id="D9BC0E66EF5D74D1F35CB265AF45B949" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
populations of Algeria and Spain from those of Egypt, although in a subsequent paper, Simon does state that 
<taxonomicName id="A8F0B2E6C0F4C5DF62AF638517639A92" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
exist in Sicily without any further comments.
</paragraph>
